<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--PrisonBlunder     09-23 0159</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Prison Blunder,0164</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Guards Unwittingly Help Murder Suspect Escape</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A murder suspect who broke his
leg jumping to freedom from a prison wall persuaded guards he was
only visiting the prison and they unwittingly helped him escape,
police said.
   Police spokesman Frans Malherbe said police were investigating
the Aug. 28 escape from Johannesburg's Diepkloof Prison by Michael
Mathebula, 24, who was accused of murder and rape.
   Guards found Mathebula lying beside the prison wall and believed
his story that he was a visitor who broke his leg jumping from a
bus, police said Thursday.
   The guards arranged for an ambulance to take Mathebula to
Baragwanath Hospital in Soweto, where he vanished after being
treated, police said.
   ``If anyone is found to have been negligent, steps will be taken
against him,'' Malherbe said.
   Mathebula also is wanted in the black homeland of Bophuthatswana
on murder charges and four counts of escaping from police custody.
</TEXT>
