<2ND_LINE>PM-Park-Shooting Victim,0160</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Park Renamed in Honor of Laurie Dann Victim</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WINNETKA, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Officials have decided to rename a park
after an 8-year-old boy shot and killed by a woman who stormed into
an elementary school last spring.
   The Winnetka Park District board voted 5-2 Thursday to name
Edgewood Park after Nicholas Corwin.
   The child was killed when Laurie Dann entered the Hubbard Woods
School during a shooting rampage May 20, wounding four
second-graders and one other person before killing herself.
   Some people opposed the board's action, arguing the child's name
would remind children of the shooting and reopen wounds in the
village that are just now beginning to close.
   But one of the speakers at the board meeting, 9-year-old
Jennifer Covelle, made a simple plea for the park's new name.
   ``I don't know what the big deal is,'' she said. ``It doesn't
remind me of the shooting, it reminds me of Nicky.''
