<2ND_LINE>PM-France-Train Crash,0096</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>One Killed, About 50 Injured As Train Plows into Truck</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VOIRON, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A train slammed into a tanker truck at a
rail crossing today, killing the conductor and injuring about 50
passengers, police said.
   Rescue workers said the injuries were not serious.
   Several cars of the high-speed train derailed on impact,
officials said.
   The train was slowing as it neared the station in this town in
the Isere region, near Grenoble. The truck was apparently stalled
at the crossing, witnesses said.
   No further information was immediately available.
</TEXT>
