<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``This is a midget coup d'etat. It's not going to lift off the
ground.'' _ Druse Moslem chieftain Walid Jumblatt, on the naming of
an interim military government in Lebanon by President Amin Gemayel
after sectarian forces deadlocked over electing Gemayel's successor.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``I said, `What are you doing?' He said, `Reverend, don't nobody
say anything. I'm going to kill everybody I see.''' _ the Rev.
Clement Ferguson, on his encounter with Clemie Ferguson, an
unemployed beautician who shot to death two store clerks, a school
custodian and a policewoman before the officer's wounded partner
killed Ferguson.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``I haven't changed. The only thing that's changed about me is
I'm fatter, I got bigger cigars and a little more money.'' _ Frank
Dileo, one of the highest-paid agents in show business whose only
client is Michael Jackson, on being honored by his hometown of
Pittsburgh with a ``Frank Dileo Day.''
