<HEAD>US Official Urges Further Immediate Aid To Flood-ravaged
Bangladesh</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A U.S. aid official back from viewing flood
damage in Bangladesh is urging that the United States provide
further aid and health supplies to victims in that country,
officials said Thursday.
   State Department spokesman Charles Redman told reporters that
the principal recommendation of Jay F. Morris, deputy administrator
of the Agency for International Development, was for immediate
additional food aid.
   Redman said Morris also urged providing more health supplies to
combat waterborn diarrheal diseases.
