multilateral effort to identify and resolve on a regional basis the
long-term causes of flooding in Bangladesh,'' he said.
   Morris made his recommendations in a report to President Reagan,
said AID spokesman John Metelsky.
   The United States already has provided $151 million worth of aid
to the flood victims, including 10,000 metric tons of wheat and
seeds to replant destroyed crops, Metelsky said.
   He said the United States also had sent 2.8 million packets of
oral-rehydration tablets to keep chidren from dying from diarrhea,
10 million water-purification tablets and other medical supplies.
