<1ST_LINE>r w AM-US-SouthAfrica     09-23 0334</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-US-South Africa,330</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>U.S. Says Activists Agreed Not To Have Contact With Media</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-South Africa</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The South African activists at the U.S.
Consulate in Johannesburg agreed when they took refuge at the
facility that they would not have contact with the news media, the
State Department said Thursday.
   Black activist Winnie Mandela, who visited the consultate on
Wednesday, had complained that U.S. officials would not let the
three men make direct contact with reporters.
   But State Department spokesman Charles Redman said the ban on
media contact was among the conditions agreed to by the men and
their legal representatives so that the consulate could function as
usual.
   ``These guidelines are designed to safeguard long-term interests
of the three men and to allow our mission to carry out its normal
operations and to avoid activities incompatible with our diplomatic
presence in a foreign country,'' he said.
   Redman told reporters that a fourth man has been given temporary
refuge with the three who escaped detention in South Africa 10 days
ago. Clifford Ngcobo entered the consulate seeking refuge on
Wednesday after apparently escaping police custody during a
hospital visit, Redman said.
   ``He indicates that he is a member of the (banned) United
Democratic Front and had been in detention for five months prior to
his escape,'' said Redman. ``He is now in temporary refuge with the
three other UDF activists.''
   The situation of the first three activists is unchanged, Redman
said.
   ``They have not reached a decision on when or how they will
leave our consular premises,'' he said.
   ``We can't serve as a spokesman for them, but, when these people
arrived at the consulate, there were certain guidelines agreed on
with them,'' Redman said. ``No restrictions of any kind have been
placed on communications between the three men and their immediate
family members, their legal representatives, and the support
committee which they designated.
   ``In accordance with these agreed guidelines, the three men
themselves have not had contact with the media.''
</TEXT>
