   Massachusetts Gov. Michael Dukakis is
holding on to his lead over Republican George Bush in Dukakis'
neighbor state of Rhode Island, according to a presidential poll
released Thursday.
   The Democratic presidential nominee was favored by 53 percent of
the 411 registered Rhode Island voters surveyed, while Bush was
supported by 35 percent, according to the poll released by WPRI-TV
