   The statement, to be made public Sept. 30, comes in response to
a worldwide bishops' synod last October that condemned sexual
discrimination. The pope has also said he wanted to reflect on the
role of women at the end of a year that the church devoted to Mary,
the mother of Jesus.
   The document on the ``Dignity of Woman'' contains few surprises,
said the Vatican official, who is familiar with it. However, it
goes into considerable detail in justifying the church's denial of
the priesthood to women.
