<TEXT>
   Stock prices gave ground Thursday in selling apparently prompted
by impatience over the market's recent sluggish performance. The
Dow Jones average closed down 10.49 at 2,080.01.
   The dollar rose in quiet trading despite central bank
intervention. Gold prices fell overseas but recovered somewhat in
domestic dealings.
   Bond prices finished slightly lower in erratic trading.
   Grain and soybean futures prices finished higher in a late
rally. On other markets, copper surged; frozen pork bellies rose
sharply while livestock futures were mixed; and energy futures
mostly were higher.
</TEXT>
