<HEAD>One-Year T Bills Reach 2-Month Low</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Interest rates on 52-week Treasury bills fell
in the government's latest auction to the lowest level in two
months.
   The Treasury Department sold $9.0 billion of the bills at an
average discount rate of 7.48 percent on Thursday, down from 7.72
percent at the last auction on Aug. 25.
   The rates were the lowest since July 28 when the one-year bills
sold for 7.40 percent.
   The new discount rate understates the actual return to investors
_ 8.04 percent with a $10,000 bill selling for $9,243.70.
