<HEAD>London Shares Mixed At Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices turned mixed at midday Friday as
investors awaited the release of a key trade report next week.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was up 1
point, or 0.06 percent, at 1,789.7 at about 12:30 p.m. local time.
   Volume came to 218.4 million shares, down from 231.3 million
shares at the same time Thursday.
   Market watchers said trading was light ahead of next Tuesday's
release of British trade deficit data for August. A
larger-than-expected gap in July shook the market when it was
reported last month.
